      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BET BET HOTSHOT (6) has the hoof on the till having finished second at Shepparton in his last two appearances, the latest from a similar barrier to this. Putting it together now and this could be his chance to break through. GUNSEN ROSIE (3) drew poorly and worked before fading last start. Had been runner-up in the previous two outings and is better served by this nice draw so deserves another chance. MACHO MAORI (8) broke last time but was solid when he raced parked for fourth in a  higher-graded race prior. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and the sprint lane is in play. Contender. ALDEBARAN MAVERICK (7) draws deep but is worth some thought after working from a similar barrier but boxing on his last-start fourth at Maryborough.",
